      "message": "You\u0027re making a good point, but I\u0027m a bit lazy to do it now because it will involve large amount of rework...\n\nToday there are several \"post-run\" processings actually.\n\n1. at handleRunEnd https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/e08dda1d1e5697a16ce83375123429ec754270aa/src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/results.go#265\n2. at end of processMessages https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/e08dda1d1e5697a16ce83375123429ec754270aa/src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/results.go#504\n3. at WriteResults https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/e08dda1d1e5697a16ce83375123429ec754270aa/src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/run/results.go#86\n\nEventually we want to do all of these post-processing at the same place. However it will involve refactoring the whole structure down from run_cmd.go.\n\nWith this change 1 and 2 are merged to the same place, so I believe it\u0027s an improvement towards the goal...",
